programme.title: The Great British Bake Off

programme.desc: Theres nine bakers left in the tent and the signature challenge is a French classic - creme brulee. The technical challenge tasks the bakers with making a Spanische windtorte and the showstopper calls for a stack of tiered cheesecakes.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Its pastry week and the bakers begin with frangipane tarts for the signature challenge. The technical challenge calls for the flaouna, a traditional cheese filled pastry from Cyprus. The showstopper is the classic 70s canape, vol au vents.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: In a `Bake Off first, the entire episode is devoted to the period of history that gave birth to modern baking, the Victorians. The signature challenge is a stalwart of the Victorian dinner table, Game Pie.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: No series of `Bake Off would be complete without testing the bakers on Patisserie and what better time to do it than the quarter finals?. The five remaining bakers must work their way through childhood favourites and delicate French fancies to a mountainous choux pastry masterpiece.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: The pressure is on, as the remaining bakers must get to grips with the one of the most difficult ingredients, chocolate.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Only three of the original twelve bakers remain. Theyve made it to the final. Over 27 challenges, theyve worked their way through every baking discipline Mary and Paul have thrown at them from cakes to bread, pastry to puddings, and biscuits to chocolate.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: In Miami, wild boar sausage and house-cured bacon; in Modesto, California, tacos and a sweet and savoury waffle; in Stockton, California, an ex-NFL player slinging wings that score with the sauce.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: In Modesto, California, Portuguese sausage and a lights-out lamb burger; in Oakland, okra gumbo and a meatless spin on succulent sandwiches; in Islamorada, Florida, wicked wings and righteous pork rinds.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieri is diving into the pie. He starts in Boston to check out a beer-crust pizza and tops it with taco fixings. Also, he visits a funky joint serving a twist on apple pie in Reno, Nevada.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieris crisscrossing the nation to grab some international grub. In Dallas, a funky Thai joint serving up noodles, curry and green papaya salad. In Miami, a Latin place dealing in empanadas and a unique plantain sandwich.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieris flying with chicken and so much more. In Santa Barbara, a butcher is saucing up chicken tacos, while in Delray Beach, FL, an homage to mum includes a mouthwatering pasta. In Las Vegas, a chef is going over the top with Thai creations.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieris piling up the meat with a little sweet. In Santa Barbara, CA, a hidden gem is putting out funky fusion like Korean paella. In Florida, a Boynton Beach butcher is elevating porchetta. A Boca Raton food truck is cooking cheesecake in a jar.

programme.title: James Martins Great British Adventure
programme.desc: James is bringing his culinary tour of the UK to his neck of the woods as he spends precious time in his adopted home county of Hampshire. Hes taking his gun dog Cooper to a training session at Laverstoke before cooking an amazing seasonal dish of partridge with vegetables and a sloe gin sauce. James hangs out with his best friend Jody Scheckter, an ex-formula one racer with an epic car collection, and a surprising passion for buffalo mozzarella.

programme.title: James Martins Great British Adventure
programme.desc: James adventure brings him over the border into North Wales, where hes joined by chef Stephen Terry for this leg of his journey. Their first stop is the grand Pale Hall, where head chef Gareth Stevenson is cooking up a real treat - Moroccan-inspired Welsh lamb. James offers his own variation of Welsh lamb in the grounds of the hall, serving with gnocchi and vegetables. Next, one of James boyhood dreams comes true as he has the ultimate falconry experience.

programme.title: James Martins Great British Adventure
programme.desc: James and Paul are having a blast in Northern Ireland and theyve reached Pauls home town of Belfast, where hes giving James a personal tour of Northern Irelands capital city before they head off for a spot of golf. James pitches up his mobile kitchen right on the green to whip up a tasty dish with bacon, scallops and apples with onion rings. After all his exertion on the golf course, Paul heads just out of town to Carnbrooke Meats.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver kickstarts his new Italian cooking adventure on the Aeolian Islands, where he learns from locals how to cook stuffed squid, inspiring his grilled squid and zingy caper salsa. He also creates a Sunday lunch for all the family.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver heads to Puglia, one of the hottest food destinations in Italy, making hand-crafted pasta, a special seafood stew, and the regions answer to paella.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver heads to Naples, the pizza capital of Italy, to seek out the recipes the locals love to eat. He is blown away by acquapazza - fish poached in crazy water.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie heads to breathtaking Basilicata in search of some seriously old school Italian recipes, with the help of a family of shepherds and an 89-year-old macaroni master.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver goes to Sicily and in the foothills of Mount Etna, he receives a masterclass in Sicilian sweets and cooks up an epic tuna, prawn and pistachio spaghetti. There is also some chocolaty cannoli on the menu.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver is in Tuscany tracking down the regions hearty farmhouse cooking. There he takes spag bol to the next level and recreates a mind-blowing Jewish-Italian recipe. There is also a special beef stew with pappardelle.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver is in Rome, tracking down the fast, fresh and easy recipes the natives of the buzzing Italian capital city cook every day. He learns how to make tasty minty pea tortiglioni, and gnocchi with roasted tomato sauce and rocket pesto.

programme.title: Jamie Cooks Italy
programme.desc: It is mid-winter and Jamie Oliver is high up in the snow-capped Italian Alps cooking some great comfort food, including dumplings, mind-blowing macaroni cheese, and a classic red wine and sausage risotto.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: James is joined by Galton Blackiston, his pal and a top-class, Michelin-starred chef. They don diving suits to swim with seals, and hire an unusual mode of transport to take them around the islands. Galton visits a sea salt farm and delivers some back to James, who uses it to cook up some wonderful salt-baked sea bass. James finds an unusual restaurant situated in the middle of a post office, and finishes off the day cooking roast duck by a stunning seashore.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: James returns to one of his favourite places in the UK: the beautiful county of Cornwall. Joining him is his close pal and Michelin-starred chef Galton Blackiston. During their trip they discover some world-class Cornish ice cream, and Galton visits Newlyn fish market to pick up some Cornish cod. James cooks the cod along with Cornish oysters and a warm tartare sauce. They both round off the day with a painting challenge on Sennen beach, where they try out their oil painting skills.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: On the next leg of his UK tour, James is joined in glorious Devon by his friend and Michelin-starred chef Simon Hulstone. James visits an extraordinary mushroom farm situated in a bungalow, and makes a tasty steak and mushroom dish. Simon samples some award-winning cheese, which inspires James to make a cheese platter fit for a king. The day ends with a trip to the Art Deco splendour of Burgh Island.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: James is joined by pal and Michelin-starred chef Mark Jordan, and together they set out to explore the delights of Jersey aboard mini motor bikes. James samples the delights of one of Jerseys most famous exports, the Jersey Royal potato, and he uses them to cook up a squid risotto with a difference. Mark Jordan gets a lesson in oyster shucking, and James discovers an island speciality: Jersey black butter, which he uses to create a delicious sweet treat.

programme.title: James Martins Islands to Highlands
programme.desc: James and his wingman, top chef Mark Jordan, hop aboard their motorbikes to discover the wonderful island of Guernsey. They sample local speciality Gache cake, a seafood platter fit for a king, and James uses Guernseys wonderful dairy produce to make a delicious creamy rice pudding with chargrilled peaches. Finally, James and Mark set themselves a fishing challenge by attempting to catch the King of the Sea: the mighty turbot.
